OL,6,FAs a force, we experienced the one the
OL,7,Fhighest number of officers injured
OL,8,Fduring the disorder, and we are
OL,9,Fpleased that the report acknowledges
OL,10,Fthe immense bravery and dedication to
OL,11,Fprotecting our communities displayed
OL,12,Fby our officers and those who provided
OL,13,Fmutual aid on that day.
OL,15,F"The health and wellbeing of our
OL,16,Fofficers and staff affected by the
OL,17,Fdisorder remains a key priority for us
OL,18,Fand we will continue to deliver an
OL,19,Fenhanced wellbeing support service to
OL,20,Fthem."
